title: Google\Cloud\Orchestration\Airflow\Service\V1\EnvironmentConfig
name: EnvironmentConfig
description:
Configuration information for an environment.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.orchestration.airflow.service.v1.EnvironmentConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.gke_cluster
params.description: Output only. The Kubernetes Engine cluster used to run this environment.

params.name: data.dag_gcs_prefix
params.description: Output only. The Cloud Storage prefix of the DAGs for this environment. Although Cloud Storage objects reside in a flat namespace, a hierarchical file tree can be simulated using "/"-delimited object name prefixes. DAG objects for this environment reside in a simulated directory with the given prefix.

params.name: data.node_count
params.description: The number of nodes in the Kubernetes Engine cluster that will be used to run this environment. This field is supported for Cloud Composer environments in versions composer-1..-airflow-..*.

params.name: data.software_config
params.description: The configuration settings for software inside the environment.

params.name: data.node_config
params.description: The configuration used for the Kubernetes Engine cluster.

params.name: data.private_environment_config
params.description: The configuration used for the Private IP Cloud Composer environment.

params.name: data.web_server_network_access_control
params.description: Optional. The network-level access control policy for the Airflow web server. If unspecified, no network-level access restrictions will be applied.

params.name: data.database_config
params.description: Optional. The configuration settings for Cloud SQL instance used internally by Apache Airflow software.

params.name: data.web_server_config
params.description: Optional. The configuration settings for the Airflow web server App Engine instance.

params.name: data.encryption_config
params.description: Optional. The encryption options for the Cloud Composer environment and its dependencies. Cannot be updated.

params.name: data.maintenance_window
params.description: Optional. The maintenance window is the period when Cloud Composer components may undergo maintenance. It is defined so that maintenance is not executed during peak hours or critical time periods. The system will not be under maintenance for every occurrence of this window, but when maintenance is planned, it will be scheduled during the window. The maintenance window period must encompass at least 12 hours per week. This may be split into multiple chunks, each with a size of at least 4 hours. If this value is omitted, the default value for maintenance window will be applied. The default value is Saturday and Sunday 00-06 GMT.

params.name: data.workloads_config
params.description: Optional. The workloads configuration settings for the GKE cluster associated with the Cloud Composer environment. The GKE cluster runs Airflow scheduler, web server and workers workloads. This field is supported for Cloud Composer environments in versions composer-2..-airflow-..* and newer.

params.name: data.environment_size
params.description: Optional. The size of the Cloud Composer environment. This field is supported for Cloud Composer environments in versions composer-2..-airflow-..* and newer.

params.name: data.airflow_uri
params.description: Output only. The URI of the Apache Airflow Web UI hosted within this environment (see Airflow web interface).

params.name: data.master_authorized_networks_config
params.description: Optional. The configuration options for GKE cluster master authorized networks. By default master authorized networks feature is: - in case of private environment: enabled with no external networks allowlisted. - in case of public environment: disabled.

params.name: data.recovery_config
params.description: Optional. The Recovery settings configuration of an environment. This field is supported for Cloud Composer environments in versions composer-2..-airflow-..* and newer.

methods.name: getMaintenanceWindow
methods.description:
Optional. The maintenance window is the period when Cloud Composer components may undergo maintenance. It is defined so that maintenance is not executed during peak hours or critical time periods.

The system will not be under maintenance for every occurrence of this window, but when maintenance is planned, it will be scheduled during the window. The maintenance window period must encompass at least 12 hours per week. This may be split into multiple chunks, each with a size of at least 4 hours. If this value is omitted, the default value for maintenance window will be applied. The default value is Saturday and Sunday 00-06 GMT.
